      'story.founder.h2': "Designed and built by a network engineer.",
      'story.founder.p1': "Guardare is designed, product-managed, and led in code by Mike Cotrone, CCIE #8411 Emeritus (Routing/Switching & Voice), formerly of Cisco Advanced Services on the ISP team, with more than 28 years architecting, implementing, and supporting networks at enterprise and ISP scale.",
      'story.founder.p2': "Before VistaTech, Mike founded two companies and built successful MSP practices inside each. The first ran on Zabbix; the second on LogicMonitor. Years of operating both platforms in production — for paying customers, around the clock — taught him precisely where each shines and where each strains: the template sprawl, the per-device invoices, the weight every legacy NMS accumulates.",
